Wines[edit]
In 2001 the Lion Nathan Wine group[33] purchased a controlling interest in Australian wine companies Petaluma and Banksia, adding New Zealand wine company Wither Hills in 2002.
The company also has distribution arrangements with some wine brands through Fine Wine Partners in Australia and Distinguished Beverages in New Zealand.
Lion-owned wine brands include:[34]

Argyle (Portland, Oregon, USA)[35]
Banksia (Barossa Valley, SA; McLaren Vale, SA; Adelaide Hills, SA)[36]
Bridgewater Mill (Adelaide Hills, SA)[37]
Croser (Piccadilly Valley, SA)[38]
Knappstein (Clare Valley, SA)[39]
Mitchelton (Nagambie, Vic)[40]
Petaluma (Clare Valley, SA; Piccadilly Valley, SA; Mount Barker, SA; Coonawarra, SA)[41]
Preece (Nagambie, Vic)[42]
Smithbrook (Pemberton, WA)[43]
St Hallett (Tanunda, Barossa Valley, SA)[44]
Stonier (Mornington Peninsula, Vic)[45]
Tatachilla (McLaren Vale, SA)[46]
Wither Hills (Marlborough, NZ)[47]
