James Squire[edit]




James Squire logo


James Squire is produced by the Malt Shovel Brewery in Sydney and now that its volume is larger that what can be produced at that brewery, some of the James Squires beers are produced at various locations around Australia under the guidance of the head brewer at the Malt Shovel Brewery. The beer is named after the convict brewer James Squire, who grew Australia's first hops and created Australia's first commercial brewery.
The brewery has won various awards including: Champion Australasian Brewery, 2000 and 2003 (Australian International Beer Awards),[18] and Best Bohemian-Style Pilsener, 2008 (World Beer Cup).[19]
