Food Lion LLC is a grocery store company headquartered in Salisbury, North Carolina,[1][2] that operates more than 1,100 supermarkets in 10 states of the Southeastern United States under the Food Lion banner. With about 63,000 employees,[3] Food Lion, LLC. is currently owned by Ahold Delhaize after it was acquired by the Delhaize Group in 1974.[4][5] One of the founders was philanthropist Ralph Ketner.



